Class DatabaseTableWithTimestamps

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fluentjdbc.DatabaseTableImpl

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DatabaseQueryable<DatabaseSimpleQueryBuilder>, DatabaseTable
    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class DatabaseTableWithTimestamps
extends DatabaseTableImpl
    DatabaseTable which automatically adds created_at and updated_at columns on insert() and updated_at on update()

        Creates a DatabaseBulkInsertBuilder object to fluently generate a INSERT ... statement for a list of objects and automatically add created_at and updated_at values. Example: 
             public void saveAll(List<TagType> tagTypes, Connection connection) {
         tagTypesTable.bulkInsert(tagTypes)
             .setField("name", TagType::getName)
             .generatePrimaryKeys("id", TagType::setId)
             .execute(connection);
     }

        public <T> DatabaseBulkUpdateBuilder<T> bulkUpdate​(Iterable<T> objects)
        Creates a DatabaseBulkUpdateBuilder object to fluently generate a UPDATE ... statement for a list of objects. Example: 
             public void updateAll(List<TagType> tagTypes, Connection connection) {
